- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithms for computing a Smith form of a matrix polynomial, which is a topic related to symbolic computation.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents a new algorithm for computing the Smith form of a matrix polynomial.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper reports the performance of the algorithm in exact arithmetic for several test cases.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the Smith form is a useful tool in control theory and the paper may be of interest to researchers in this field.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a less likely category, but the paper may involve some logical reasoning in the algorithm design.
